    <item>
      <title>Re: Bard Pulling Question</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=TNZ&amp;message.id=246070#M246070</link>
      <description>The speed to bard pulls is the mez.&amp;nbsp; If there's 2 mobs, mez one, let the other aggro, and bring it to camp knowing there'll be another inc in a mo that'll need mezzing.&lt;br&gt;It's the gaps between combat that feels slow, if once you've got a mob in camp, you can run off, bring one in and let it be mezd/debuffed/slowed ready for the tank to instantly switch over,the loss of bard song whilst pulling won't be missed, and you'll get better at dashing off just as the regen/mana song has landed.&amp;nbsp; You get a bit more time to prep the pull whilst the groups fighting as they won't notice the time as much.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; If there's multiple camps of mobs near where your pulling to, leave an easy single/duo nearby if you mistime the rate of killing in camp and need to top off the groups mobs.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Controlled chain pulls is where the speed is, keep working on it and you'll find groups appreciate the speed.&amp;nbsp; Just let them know what your doing in advance to prepare for it.&lt;br&gt;(this technique is something that you'll continue to rifine the rest of your bard pulling time, so it's well worth starting when you can).&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
